                            <comment id="433355" author="yujian" created="Wed, 30 Oct 2024 17:30:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you, &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=nscfreny&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;nscfreny&quot;&gt;nscfreny&lt;/a&gt;. I just updated the patch series.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="432815" author="nscfreny" created="Sat, 26 Oct 2024 07:46:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Tested client with latest b2_15 patch series. Triggered crash doing ls on a mounted filesystem, looks like &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17696&quot; title=&quot;Kernel 6.8 client LBUG: (dcache.c:136:ll_ddelete()) ASSERTION( d_count(de) == 1 ) failed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-17696&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-17696&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Got client working with latest b2_15 patch series + cherry-pick &quot;0176629ab3 &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17696&quot; title=&quot;Kernel 6.8 client LBUG: (dcache.c:136:ll_ddelete()) ASSERTION( d_count(de) == 1 ) failed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-17696&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-17696&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; llite: remove LASSERT from ll_ddelete()&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="432812" author="yujian" created="Sat, 26 Oct 2024 05:55:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch series &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/56754&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/56754&lt;/a&gt; for Lustre b2_15 branch was updated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="432386" author="yujian" created="Wed, 23 Oct 2024 17:55:14 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;That is due to libcfs_mem.c depend on libcfs_cpt code. I had to move libcfs_cpt first before libcfs_mem.c&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thank you &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=simmonsja&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;simmonsja&quot;&gt;simmonsja&lt;/a&gt; for this info. I&apos;m back-porting &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/52923&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/52923&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9859&quot; title=&quot;libcfs simplification&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9859&quot;&gt;LU-9859&lt;/a&gt; lnet: move CPT handling to LNet&quot;).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="432322" author="simmonsja" created="Wed, 23 Oct 2024 13:25:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That is due to libcfs_mem.c depend on libcfs_cpt code. I had to move libcfs_cpt first before libcfs_mem.c&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="432307" author="nscfreny" created="Wed, 23 Oct 2024 11:32:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Build OK but there seem to be a circular module dependency?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;depmod: ERROR: Cycle detected: libcfs -&amp;gt; lnet -&amp;gt; libcfs
depmod: ERROR: Found 2 modules in dependency cycles!&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="432293" author="yujian" created="Wed, 23 Oct 2024 07:02:45 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;More patches are needed for Lustre b2_15 branch.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
